01:11:46,140 --> 01:11:48,380
And what is it that strikes out across the desert?

905
01:11:48,380 --> 01:11:53,660
Well it's the black horse, which is formed from the bones of the virgin buried in the

906
01:11:53,660 --> 01:11:55,820
tomb in the old country.

907
01:11:55,820 --> 01:12:02,140
So the anima, the soul we might say, has become dead, dry, dusty bones within the reign of

908
01:12:02,140 --> 01:12:04,220
an old kingdom.

909
01:12:04,220 --> 01:12:08,820
And once the king decided to lay himself to rest, so to speak, the soul jumps up.

910
01:12:08,820 --> 01:12:12,500
It runs out into the unknown until it finds a new green pasture.

911
01:12:12,500 --> 01:12:16,940
And by following it, following the drive of the soul, the black magician finds the keys

912
01:12:16,940 --> 01:12:24,940
to paradise, the treasure hard to obtain, the holy grail, the return to the walled garden.

913
01:12:24,940 --> 01:12:31,460
Jung writes, quote, the two magicians are indeed two aspects of the wise old man, the

914
01:12:31,460 --> 01:12:36,940
superior master and teacher, the archetype of the spirit who symbolizes the pre-existent

915
01:12:36,940 --> 01:12:40,260
meaning hidden in the chaos of life.

916
01:12:40,260 --> 01:12:45,020
He is the father of the soul, and yet the soul in some miraculous manner is also his

917
01:12:45,020 --> 01:12:51,940
virgin mother, for which reason he was called by the alchemists the first son of the mother.

918
01:12:51,940 --> 01:12:57,300
The black magician and the black horse correspond to the descent into darkness and the dreams

919
01:12:57,300 --> 01:12:59,300
mentioned earlier.

920
01:12:59,300 --> 01:13:03,460
What an inappropriately hard lesson for a young student of theology.

921
01:13:03,460 --> 01:13:07,900
Fortunately, he was not in the least sense aware that the father of all prophets had

922
01:13:07,900 --> 01:13:13,220
spoken to him in the dream and placed a great secret almost within his grasp.

923
01:13:13,220 --> 01:13:19,340
